author: cmpilato
msg: On the 'issue-3148-dev' branch: Rework the way failed-externals
notification is done so that errors that happen before we official
start messing with the external working copy look a little different
than those that happen *while* processing the external working copy,
and to maximize the amount of useful error information we can print.
No, this still doesn't pass the test suite.
* subversion/svn/notify.c
(notify): In the 'svn_wc_notify_failed_external' case, manage the
nb->in_external flag appropriately, and print the detailed error
(possible with another line that describes which external working
copy had the problem).
* subversion/libsvn_client/externals.c
(handle_external_item_change_wrapper): Clear the external error here.
